Stephen Sondheim's Into the Woods









Media contact: Noelle Lemoine, communications assistant; tele: (413) 597-4277; email: [email protected]
WILLIAMSTOWN, Mass., Nov. 28, 2006 — Are you certain what you wish is what you want?
Williams College Cap & Bells is proud to present Stephen Sondheim and James Lapine’s Tony Award-winning musical, Into the Woods, directed by Ren McDermott ’07 and Eric Kang ’09.
The musical features fairy tales, such as “Jack and the Beanstalk,” “Cinderella,” “Little Red Ridinghood,” “Sleeping Beauty,” “Snow White” and “Rapunzel,” but deals with consequences that traditional fairy tales conveniently ignore. Ultimately, all of the characters in the stories must deal with what happens after “happily ever after.”
Into the Woods opens December 7 at 8 p.m. There will also be performances December 8 and 9 at 8 p.m. and a 2 p.m. matinee on December 9. There will be a special Family Matinee on Sunday, December 10, with a one-act “family friendly” performance at 2 p.m. All performances will be held in the ’62 Center’s Adams Memorial Theatre. Tickets are $5 per person ($3 for the Family Matinee) and can be purchased by calling the ’62 Center Box Office at (413) 597-2425.
The cast, crew and orchestra of Into the Woods consists solely of Williams College Students.
Cast: Davern Wright (Baker), Greta Wilson (Baker’s Wife), Hannah Lum (Witch), Paul Rogers (Mysterious Man/Narrator), Richard McDowell (Jack), Hannah Baker (Jack’s Mother, Kate McCurdy (Cinderella), Miles Klee (Cinderella’s Prince/Wolf), Margot Bernstein (Little Red Ridinghood), Jessica Kopcho (Rapunzel), Daniel Wollin (Rapunzel’s Prince), Julie Esteves (Cinderella’s Stepmother), Caitlin Eley (Lucinda), Natalie Smith (Florinda), Jason Kohn (Cinderella’s Father), Lisa Sloan (Cinderella’s Mother/Granny/Giant), and Edgardo Costas-Bracero (Steward).
Creative Team: Ren McDermott (Director), Eric Kang (Music Director), Emily Chepiga (Assistant Director), Noah Smith-Drelich (Rehearsal Pianist), Peter Schmidt (Stage Manager), Jenny Schnabl (Assitant Stage Manager), Edwin Johnson (Set/Prop Design), Kate Foster (Light Design), Toby Schneider (Sound/Poster/Program Design), Ruth Steinhardt (Costume Design), and Edgardo Costas-Bracero (Hair/Makeup Design) Orchestral Pit: Matthew Wollin (flute) Avalon Gulley (clarinet), Stephen Webste (bass clarinet), Katie Quinn (horn), Amanda Korman (trumpet), Eugenie Du (violin), Sarah MacWright (violin), Michele Chinitz (viola), Sarah Martin (viola), Katie Palmer (cello), Michael Marchinetti (bass), Noah Smith-Drelich (piano), Sam Kapala (percussion).
***
For building locations on the Williams campus, please consult the map outside the driveway entrance to the Security Office located in Hopkins Hall on Main Street (Rte. 2), next to the Thompson Memorial Chapel, or call the Office of Public Affairs (413) 597-4279. The map can also be found on the web at www.williams.edu/home/campusmap/
END



